"{\"uid\": \"meetings.skift.com-2024-07-30-lessons-for-event-planners-from-the-paris-olympics-take-risks-but-have-a-plan-b\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Photo Caption: The Eiffel Tower lights up the night for the Paris 2024 Olympics opening ceremony, surrounded by a crowd of spectators.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics opening ceremony in Paris unfolded under an unexpected veil of rain, adding an unplanned layer of drama.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 169, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.917649906762221e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this was just the beginning.\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Select a question above orask something else  Paris held the first-ever Olympics opening ceremony outside a stadium.\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 334, \"end\": 339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.917649906762221e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes paraded\\u00a0not by foot but by boat, waving flags from pontoons on the Seine.\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 481, \"end\": 486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.183012484490956e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The four-hour event, which included more than 3,000 musical artists, dancers, actors, and circus performers, was marred by persistent rain, ranging from light showers to intense downpours.\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The unrelenting weather caused several logistical problems.\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Technical difficulties plagued some floats, leading to temporary power outages and interruptions, while elaborate costumes became drenched.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Evan Babins, event manager for global financial technology platformIntuit, noted that a protective structure along the river could have mitigated the impact of the rain on attendees.\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 1062, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When they decided the opening ceremony would be on the river, they should have planned for weather issues.\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1171, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tents, a temporary structure, coverage for the cameras so viewers did not see raindrops on the lens would have helped,\\\" said Babins.\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He adds that more thought should have been put into the fact that this was ahybrid event.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They did not connect the in-person audience with those watching virtually,\\\" said Babins.\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rain was not the only challenge.\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a notable blunder, South Korean athletes were mistakenly announced as representing the Democratic People's Republic of Korea - or North Korea - rather than the Republic of Korea.\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1552, \"end\": 1558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9626313529926012, \"rank\": 0.03869965225324022, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999999736247, \"rank\": 2.327696029217419e-11, \"text\": \"North Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Olympic Committee spokesperson Mark Adams acknowledged the error, stating, \\\"An operational mistake was made.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1752, \"end\": 1762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"score\": 0.5137413298826524, \"rank\": 0.45833333333321225, \"text\": \"Mark Adams\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We can only apologize, in an evening of so many moving parts, that this mistake was made.\\\"\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In another opening ceremony glitch, the Olympic flag featuring the five rings was hoisted upside down toward the end of the ceremony.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 2055, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are some who feel the Olympic opening ceremony drifted away from its \\\"why.\\\"\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Was this ceremony designed to honor the athletes?\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you ask me, no, not at all,\\\" said Aleksandra Panyukhina, an events marketing executive.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The whole thing was designed for the TV viewers, not the crowds in the streets, so no surprise people did not stick around for long.\\\"\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony, curated by artistic director Thomas Jolly, stirred emotion, not all positive.\", \"from\": 2417, \"to\": 2508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2460, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9889076489003665, \"rank\": 0.007865057308106736, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Atableaudepicting the Greek god Dionysus and an ancient festival honoring him was criticized for being a parody of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper.\\\"\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.8833536014111879, \"rank\": 0.12816350329623225, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.276111282373662e-23, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2625, \"end\": 2642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.5622005968084854e-21, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Drag artists and dancers were featured in the scene.\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2716, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly defended the tableau.\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Last Supper wasn't the inspiration behind the scene.\", \"from\": 2746, \"to\": 2803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dionysus arrives at the table because he is the Greek God of celebration and that sequence is called \\\"festivity.\\\"\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2804, \"end\": 2812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.276111282373662e-23, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2852, \"end\": 2857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.8833536014111879, \"rank\": 0.12816350329623225, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympic organizers issued an apology to those who were offended but that wasn't enough for some.\", \"from\": 2919, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2919, \"end\": 2924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.917649906762221e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Bishops' Conference, which represents the country's Catholic bishops,said in a statementthat the scene was a \\\"mockery and derision of Christianity.\\\"\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3027, \"end\": 3033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9929640632845671, \"rank\": 0.005207090882119567, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3086, \"end\": 3094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999994915925, \"rank\": 3.852611603375461e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 3168, \"end\": 3180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999280102140459, \"rank\": 7.198560643949892e-05, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Telecommunications provider C Spiresaidit was pulling all its advertising from the Olympics as a result of the scene.\", \"from\": 3184, \"to\": 3301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In today's polarized world, people are more hypercritical than ever.\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Planning something on this scale was no easy task.\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I applaud the event planners for taking a chance,\\\" said Nicola Kastner, founder of The Event Strategist and the CEO of Event Leaders Exchange (ELX).\", \"from\": 3424, \"to\": 3572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3480, \"end\": 3486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\", \"score\": 0.9999029517067715, \"rank\": 9.678574530056389e-05, \"text\": \"Nicola\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 3507, \"end\": 3516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Event\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0016424424205576e-15, \"text\": \"The Event\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Event\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Event\"}, {\"begin\": 3567, \"end\": 3570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elche\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ELX\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elche\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The evening ended with a performance by Celine Dion from the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3614, \"end\": 3625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.885975916505612e-36, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her first public appearance since being diagnosed with stiff-person syndrome in 2022.\", \"from\": 3649, \"to\": 3734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even with the snafus, Babins thought the ceremony was a success.\", \"from\": 3736, \"to\": 3800, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I loved that it wasn't in an arena and the way it paid tribute to Paris.\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3868, \"end\": 3873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.917649906762221e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought taking the risk to do it differently was a great move,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3875, \"to\": 3949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Trish Knox, owner of TK Events, praises the ceremony's creativity.\", \"from\": 3951, \"to\": 4017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3951, \"end\": 3956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trish_Stratus\", \"score\": 0.9999732399448362, \"rank\": 1.4142974177445146e-05, \"text\": \"Trish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trish_Stratus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trish_Stratus\"}, {\"begin\": 3957, \"end\": 3961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Knox\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5286810000162958e-24, \"text\": \"Knox\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Knox\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Knox\"}, {\"begin\": 3972, \"end\": 3974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TK_Samuels\", \"score\": 0.9999999759852475, \"rank\": 2.3856557577964892e-08, \"text\": \"TK\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TK_Samuels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TK_Samuels\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They threw out the playbook to do something different.\", \"from\": 4018, \"to\": 4073, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't perfect but that's what happens when you are the first at something,\\\" said Knox.\", \"from\": 4074, \"to\": 4164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4159, \"end\": 4163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Knox\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5286810000162958e-24, \"text\": \"Knox\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Knox\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Knox\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many event planners will be watching theclosing ceremonyon August 11.\", \"from\": 4166, \"to\": 4235, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike the opening ceremony held in the heart of Paris, this show will be confined to theStade de France.\", \"from\": 4236, \"to\": 4341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4285, \"end\": 4290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.917649906762221e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4334, \"end\": 4340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9983879625871667, \"rank\": 0.001422167611406499, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over a hundred performers, acrobats, dancers, and circus artists will be featured.\", \"from\": 4342, \"to\": 4424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:contingency,Olympics,Opening Ceremony,Paris  The Paris Olympics featured a groundbreaking opening ceremony on the Seine River, which faced logistical issues due to persistent rain and technical difficulties.\", \"from\": 4426, \"to\": 4638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4452, \"end\": 4468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.999820892358024, \"rank\": 0.00010244114365643589, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 4469, \"end\": 4474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.917649906762221e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Missteps included incorrect announcements and flag mishandling, while artistic choices, such as a controversial tableau, led to public criticism and a sponsor withdrawing support.\", \"from\": 4639, \"to\": 4818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite these challenges, the event was praised for its creativity and risk-taking approach.\", \"from\": 4819, \"to\": 4911, \"entities\": []}]}"